---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Work with me | Igor Tarasenko"
  description="Book a 30-minute call to debug your AI feature, agent loop, or iOS architecture problem. $100 paid sessions, or a free discovery call."
>
  <Header />
  <div class="grid">
    <main id="main-content" class="content prose">
      <h1 class="page-h1">Work with me</h1>

      <p class="page-lede">
        Got an AI feature stuck between a demo and production? Book a call.
        You bring the problem, I bring 30 minutes of focused attention.
      </p>

      <div class="cta-stack">
        <a class="cta cta-primary" href="https://cal.com/tarasenko/30min">
          Book a 30-minute call, $100 &rarr;
        </a>
        <p class="cta-note">
          Paid sessions get you the full focus and a written follow-up. Most
          problems get unstuck in one call.
        </p>

        <a class="cta cta-secondary" href="https://cal.com/tarasenko/discovery">
          Not sure yet? Book a free discovery call &rarr;
        </a>
        <p class="cta-note">
          15 minutes, no pitch. We figure out if I&rsquo;m the right person
          for your problem.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>What I&rsquo;m useful for</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Debugging an LLM integration or agent loop.</li>
        <li>Reviewing an AI architecture before the build starts.</li>
        <li>Diagnosing RAG, tool-calling, prompt, or context problems.</li>
        <li>Setting up practical AI coding workflows for your team.</li>
        <li>Fixing SwiftUI or iOS architecture and build-time issues.</li>
        <li>Untangling a repo, CI, modularization, or DX bottleneck.</li>
        <li>Deciding whether a prototype is worth productionizing.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I&rsquo;m not useful for</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Writing your prompts.</li>
        <li>Picking your model.</li>
        <li>Building a chatbot wrapper around an API.</li>
        <li>Anything without a real user on the other end.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Track record</h2>

      <p>
        WhisperBoard 4.8&#9733; on the App Store. mcp-browser-use ~900 stars.
        Codementor 5.0 across 30 sessions. Five years at Uber on
        server-driven UI then payments. In-house now at a large enterprise
        SaaS company, building the agent-assisted dev environment and the
        guardrails around it.
      </p>

      <h2>Other ways in</h2>

      <p>
        Prefer Codementor? <a href="https://www.codementor.io/@saik0s">Book there instead</a>.
        Need something longer than a call? A few weeks in the repo, fixed-fee
        and scope-locked.
        <a href="mailto:igor@tarasenko.dev?subject=Engagement">Email me</a>
        with what&rsquo;s broken and we&rsquo;ll see if it fits.
      </p>

      <Footer />
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .cta-stack {
    margin: 32px 0 48px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .cta {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 16px 24px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 17px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    text-decoration: none;
    line-height: 1.3;
    transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
  }
  .cta-primary {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--bg);
    border-color: var(--ink);
  }
  .cta-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg);
  }
  .cta-secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-top: 16px;
  }
  .cta-secondary:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .cta-note {
    margin: 4px 0 16px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>
